      "name": "Does a Brisbane seller have to allow extra inspections after the contract has gone unconditional?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "No. Under the standard REIQ contract used in Queensland, once a contract is unconditional the buyer is only entitled to one pre-settlement inspection within three business days before settlement. Any access beyond that, such as bringing in tradespeople, designers, renovators or removalists, is a courtesy the seller may grant or refuse. The seller remains in possession until settlement and has the legal right to control who enters the property."
      }
